The paper proposes a new approach to partially observable planning using Thompson Sampling, which is a popular technique in machine learning and reinforcement learning. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on benchmark problems, which suggests that it falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and decision-making in large POMDPs, which could also place it under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Robotics (cs.RO), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithmic approach, which could also place it under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category.
